<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Fourth</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, I killed some Mini-Bosses last night in Plane of Storms for some BoT keys for people. The tank during our first fight in the Forest was a huge frog. There was no CH chain and they told the Warriors to just try and look pretty while avoiding agro. That was kind of sad and I can see how that’s a slap in the face. They just said “Someone heal the frog every so often.”<br>
<br>
I’ve seen Verant tune content to preserve spells forever. (Quad kiting and AoE groups come to mind.)<br>
<br>
It still seems unfair for them to make Charm worthless as a fix for the current problem. I definitely think certain areas (Like that Boss in Bastion of thunder where you can get to them with invis and use the portal as an instant escape) need to be tuned in general, and not just based on Charm.<br>
<br>
With that said.. I like the ideas some people have had of reducing the effectiveness of a charmed mob. Lower it’s regen. Lower its damage output. Heck, lower its health. (Although I could see that being used to soften up a mob, then break charm and get an easy kill.)<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Fifth</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->, for you potty mouths out there (Enchanters and Mages alike.) the words A-hole and moron are BOTH wrong and should BOTH be reprimanded. Let’s try to fight kindly here.<br>
