<br>
Most of the enchanters that have come posting here are just slandering and throwing personal insults and attacks in.  Then they don't make any valid claims.<br>
<br>
Death is not a valid claim<br>
<br>
Graveyards and massive exp pretty much make up for a death (without rez) even 20-30 mins easily while solo.<br>
<br>
You have no chance to lose your corpse.<br>
<br>
How willing would you be to go take on a room full of named if you have to run back there and get your corpse from under their nose?  Not bloody likely I'd wager.<br>
<br>
So what if you die?  You start back with full mana just get your gear back on in a few mins and go at it again.  Rez?  Well then you have to wait what...5 mins of medding w/mana regen to get all your mana back?<br>
<br>
In POP, if you die you die.  Just wait at the GY and wait for your corpse to spawn, loot it then be on your way.<br>
<br>
Other zones you have to go get your corpse yourself.  I don't see chanters going into places like Howling Stones solo and doing the same tactics there.  Why not?<br>
<br>
Because they know for sure that if they die, they'd have to get back in there and try to get to their corpse again...which ain't easy to do in that place alone.  Been there, done that (I zoned in with another mage, neither of us knowing that the zone-in was unsafe and after 3 cr attempts I got my items and successfully gated out).<br>
<br>
Risk vs reward?  There is no risk in POP, only that you'll fail and will get another chance as soon as your corpse is back.<br>
<br>
And I'm also one of the people who is 'jealous' of the amount of EXP that can be earned per hour with this thing.  I am having to plan out what AA points I am going to spend on because it'll be a while before I get enough to spend on something else big again.<br>
<br>
1 AA in 20 mins, i'd just fill up everything possible.  And i'm sure that they are too.  So yes, I think its crap that other people have to sit lfg for hours, hoping to group with other people that are good players and won't end up getting you killed every time a mob is pulled, while chanters are running around farming AA like its plat.<br>
<br>
No one class should be able to hit 65 then have /GOD MODE ON<br>
<br>
Multiplayer game with different classes and skills, they should have to work together more the higher one gets.<br>
Not become totally independent.<br>
<br>
*/rant off<br>
