<br>
One good suggestion is to include a slow component of 50% or so in the charm. (Or Atk debuff, or anything that will cut dps down to approx rogue level). A chanter will never replace a rogue in the 'damage dealer' spot then since there will still be all the problems inherant from having a 500 dps bomb ready to explode on the group at any moment.<br>
<br>
The other suggestion I think reasonable is to add a recast time to CoD; say 5 mins. To me this gets charm back to what I believe was the original intent - to temporarily turn the tide of battle, one mob against its former allies (but what do I know about that). 500 dps against you turned to 500 dps for you is a 1000 dps swing after all, that's still a HUGE ability when you think about it.<br>
<br>
DC I think *is* well balanced in PoP. Noonie said it well when she said that she could practically go afk when being beaten on by one of those light blue things. I recall they have been parsed at 50dps or so, meaning you could be beaten on for a minute without really breaking sweat, hardly unreasonable in the least. And if the chanter dies or goes ld or the pet dies, it's gone; there usually isnt a pet available in camp. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=noonievioletskies>NoonieVioletskies</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Sage</span><br>  Posts: 1545<br> <font color=#333333>(1/9/03 6:54:58 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm32.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=443.topic&index=127>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.sebminas.com/eq/baby.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Enchanters Overpowered ?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr><br>
