Zero risk? what if one of them is off time? what if one of them lags, Oh no, a mean dragon is comming to beat them in within an inch of there life and wallah, they die. I know many wizards that died Manaburning these Kunark Dragons. While the risk was very minimal, it was there, just as the risk is very minimal with CoD.<br>
<br>
How many classes whines for Manaburn to be nerfed? Alot, all except wizards. Was manaburn a great ability? undoubtably so. Did people cry for a nerf when the ability first came out? no. But when the wizards abused manaburn, killing kunark dragons with it, people from all around norrath called for a nerf and were outraged by it.<br>
<br>
The same holds true for CoD almost completely, only guess what? I addition to being able to farm mobs that groups/raids were suppossed to do, you can use this for xping also. Of course people are going to call for a nerf for this. It's more powerful than manaburn ever was and we all know how many threads on every board was started over manaburn being overpowered.<br>
<br>
Abuse your power and people will want it taken away.<br>
<br>
My guess is that if enchanters would have never solo'd those BoT named, no one would have called for a nerf. You have those enchanters that abused the spell to blame for people wanting it nerfed.<br>
<br>
<br>
