<br>
Tuning is what (Since day one) I'm in favor of.<br>
<br>
Nerf to me means to make something harmless. (Such as turn something into a Nerf ball.. harmless and fluffy.)<br>
<br>
To tune something means to bring it more in line with &quot;The Vision&quot; of game merchanics.<br>
<br>
I've always stated that I want things tuned. And I still wanna puke when I hear someone say &quot;Nerf&quot;.<br>
<br>
I also agree that I didn't understand the magnitude of the harm that CoD does to PoP encounters in general.<br>
<br>
The other argument I don't find too compelling is the &quot;They get an AA every 20 minutes!&quot;... there are so many classes that can Quad/AE and do special things. (I can't go mow down Fungus grove free of risk for instance.) I don't complain about those things, so I'm not gonna complain about Chanters getting fast exp.<br>
<br>
It does sound like some difference of opinion (But less than we started with for sure.) and some misunderstanding. The written word is a horrible form of communication, that's for sure.<br>
